  "conclusion": "1. Progressive neurodegenerative changes consistent with Alzheimer's disease. Moderate bilateral hippocampal atrophy, progressed from mild on the April 2022 comparison study. 2. Mildly progressive generalized cortical atrophy, most prominent in the temporal and parietal lobes. 3. Chronic small-vessel ischemic white matter changes, Fazekas grade 1-2, mildly progressed. 4. No acute infarct, intracranial hemorrhage, mass lesion, or hydrocephalus.",
